1
00:00:01,040 --> 00:00:03,000
Sin. Sin.

2
00:00:04,160 --> 00:00:05,720
Come back and talk to me.

3
00:00:06,320 --> 00:00:08,400
Who are you to order me around?
You're not my father.

4
00:00:08,480 --> 00:00:09,840
If you want me to go back,

5
00:00:09,920 --> 00:00:11,800
then stand up. And I'll go back.

6
00:00:11,880 --> 00:00:13,680
You're getting out of hand, huh?

7
00:00:13,760 --> 00:00:16,840
I'm not some nobody
for you to step over like this.

8
00:00:17,480 --> 00:00:19,720
If you take even one more step out,

9
00:00:20,400 --> 00:00:22,320
don't ever come back. This is my house!

10
00:00:22,400 --> 00:00:25,000
If Aunt Nong hadn't asked me to stay,
I wouldn't want to live here.

11
00:00:25,080 --> 00:00:26,920
Sin! Sin!

12
00:00:27,000 --> 00:00:28,280
Come here and apologize to me!

13
00:00:28,360 --> 00:00:30,120
Hey! Where are you going?

14
00:00:30,200 --> 00:00:31,200
Sin!

15
00:00:31,280 --> 00:00:32,439
I said get back here!

16
00:00:32,520 --> 00:00:33,520
Come apologize to me!

17
00:00:34,280 --> 00:00:35,120
Get off! Hey!

18
00:00:35,200 --> 00:00:36,760
Hey! Hey!

19
00:00:37,360 --> 00:00:38,600
You bastard! You piece of trash!

20
00:00:38,680 --> 00:00:40,520
Are you trying to kill me?!

21
00:00:40,600 --> 00:00:42,640
Sin! Anong!

22
00:00:43,160 --> 00:00:44,680
Come look at your nephew!

23
00:00:47,320 --> 00:00:48,320
Anong!

24
00:01:14,320 --> 00:01:15,040
Anong.

25
00:01:16,160 --> 00:01:17,440
What the hell are you doing?

26
00:01:19,840 --> 00:01:20,680
Anong.

27
00:04:04,280 --> 00:04:05,920
-Mr. Warat.
-Go inside.

28
00:04:09,320 --> 00:04:11,880
Is this what you meant
by "somewhere you like"?

29
00:04:11,960 --> 00:04:14,000
This is the Chairwoman's office.

30
00:04:15,000 --> 00:04:16,800
Didn't you say it yourself

31
00:04:16,880 --> 00:04:20,440
that the place that could give us
the most truth was Grandma's office?

32
00:04:21,360 --> 00:04:23,080
But not like this.

33
00:04:23,160 --> 00:04:25,360
Not by sneaking in like this.

34
00:04:25,440 --> 00:04:27,920
If someone sees us, you're dead.

35
00:04:28,440 --> 00:04:30,400
And there's a security camera too.

36
00:04:31,880 --> 00:04:34,360
You think I'd barge into
my Grandma's office

37
00:04:34,440 --> 00:04:35,840
without planning anything?

38
00:04:37,680 --> 00:04:39,440
I still don't feel good about this.

39
00:04:39,520 --> 00:04:41,160
Just hurry and handle your business.

40
00:04:41,240 --> 00:04:42,680
"Your business"?

41
00:04:43,200 --> 00:04:44,600
I don't think so.

42
00:04:44,680 --> 00:04:46,000
It's our business.

43
00:04:48,360 --> 00:04:49,720
I found out

44
00:04:49,800 --> 00:04:51,760
that Grandma keeps some old albums.

45
00:04:52,280 --> 00:04:54,440
They should be in that cabinet.

46
00:04:55,320 --> 00:04:56,440
You can try

47
00:04:57,080 --> 00:04:58,360
touching things.

48
00:04:59,120 --> 00:05:01,200
Maybe you'll see something.

49
00:05:02,560 --> 00:05:03,800
Hey.

50
00:05:03,880 --> 00:05:06,360
But that cabinet has a passcode lock.

51
00:05:06,440 --> 00:05:08,080
Can you even open it?

52
00:05:08,680 --> 00:05:12,040
I got into Grandma's room
using my birth date as the code.

53
00:05:12,560 --> 00:05:15,440
Do you think the code for that cabinet

54
00:05:16,520 --> 00:05:17,840
will be hard for me?

55
00:05:20,440 --> 00:05:22,320
That means Grandma really loves you.

56
00:05:22,400 --> 00:05:24,440
That's why she sets
everything to your birthday.

57
00:05:24,520 --> 00:05:25,520
Not really.

58
00:05:26,200 --> 00:05:27,240
It's just easy to remember.

59
00:05:48,160 --> 00:05:49,480
I don't know who these people are.

60
00:05:50,000 --> 00:05:53,280
There are so many.
We might have to come back again.

61
00:05:55,440 --> 00:05:57,240
I'm not doing this again.

62
00:05:57,320 --> 00:05:59,160
Let's end it tonight.

63
00:05:59,760 --> 00:06:00,760
Let me help look.

64
00:06:10,080 --> 00:06:12,840
If you recognize anyone, tell me.

65
00:06:13,640 --> 00:06:16,760
But I don't see anyone who looks like
the people we're searching for.

66
00:06:18,880 --> 00:06:22,120
If we go through all of this,
we'll be here till morning.

67
00:06:23,960 --> 00:06:26,720
Mr. Warat,
I think we should try this way instead.

68
00:06:32,280 --> 00:06:35,000
I'm not hardworking or anything.
I was just sick of staying home,

69
00:06:35,080 --> 00:06:36,880
so I came to finish some work.

70
00:06:36,960 --> 00:06:38,800
I have a presentation early tomorrow.

71
00:06:38,880 --> 00:06:41,000
<i>Are you sure you're not joining me here?</i>

72
00:06:41,080 --> 00:06:42,280
<i>I'm chilling.</i>

73
00:06:43,040 --> 00:06:45,600
I'm not joining you.
And don't drink too much,

74
00:06:45,680 --> 00:06:47,400
or you won't be able to work tomorrow.

75
00:06:53,800 --> 00:06:54,880
Warat's car?

76
00:07:04,160 --> 00:07:05,360
You're smart.

77
00:07:10,120 --> 00:07:13,520
Your compliments are never to be trusted.

78
00:07:13,600 --> 00:07:14,840
I'm really complimenting you.

79
00:07:16,760 --> 00:07:19,680
It's better than looking one by one.

80
00:07:20,440 --> 00:07:21,480
There are too many photos.

81
00:07:21,560 --> 00:07:24,520
Let's take pictures of all of them,
then zoom in and look later.

82
00:07:38,160 --> 00:07:39,880
I haven't even pressed capture yet.

83
00:07:41,440 --> 00:07:42,480
Hey!

84
00:07:47,040 --> 00:07:51,160
I never imagined
I'd run into someone at this hour.

85
00:07:51,240 --> 00:07:52,840
How dare you

86
00:07:53,440 --> 00:07:54,680
take pictures of me?

87
00:07:54,760 --> 00:08:00,240
At first, I thought
I'd just use it as wallpaper.

88
00:08:00,320 --> 00:08:02,320
But thinking about it now,

89
00:08:02,840 --> 00:08:05,680
I think I should report it
to the police instead.

90
00:08:05,760 --> 00:08:08,240
Because this is the Chairwoman's office.

91
00:08:08,320 --> 00:08:09,840
Do I need to remind you

92
00:08:09,920 --> 00:08:12,960
that you shouldn't be here,
especially at this hour?

93
00:08:13,040 --> 00:08:14,400
What exactly are you two doing here?

94
00:08:15,040 --> 00:08:17,800
I think the one
who needs a reminder is you.

95
00:08:18,720 --> 00:08:21,560
Have you lost your mind?

96
00:08:21,640 --> 00:08:23,560
This is Vanich Mall's office.

97
00:08:24,440 --> 00:08:26,600
And I'm the owner.

98
00:08:26,680 --> 00:08:29,400
So I can come and go whenever I want.

99
00:08:30,280 --> 00:08:31,280
But you?

100
00:08:31,800 --> 00:08:33,159
Why are you here at this hour?

101
00:08:34,280 --> 00:08:36,600
I'm here to work.

102
00:08:37,200 --> 00:08:38,880
If you don't believe me,

103
00:08:38,960 --> 00:08:41,559
there's someone who can confirm it.

104
00:08:41,640 --> 00:08:44,080
The Chairwoman. The owner of this room.

105
00:08:46,280 --> 00:08:50,320
I'm curious too about
what the Chairwoman will think

106
00:08:50,400 --> 00:08:51,640
about what's on my phone.

107
00:08:53,080 --> 00:08:55,000
In just a few hours.

108
00:08:55,520 --> 00:08:56,840
Be patient.

109
00:08:59,440 --> 00:09:00,960
-Sin.
-Don't follow him.

110
00:09:03,280 --> 00:09:06,040
But he's going to show
the photos to your Grandma.

111
00:09:06,840 --> 00:09:07,920
I think

112
00:09:08,960 --> 00:09:11,400
he's saving them
to use against us in a bigger way.

113
00:09:11,480 --> 00:09:14,520
Hey, that's even worse.

114
00:09:14,600 --> 00:09:15,760
It's fine.

115
00:09:17,040 --> 00:09:18,960
We'll figure out how to handle it.

116
00:09:20,040 --> 00:09:22,680
Have you figured out how?

117
00:09:23,320 --> 00:09:24,160
Not yet.

118
00:09:26,240 --> 00:09:27,240
Put the albums back.

119
00:09:40,600 --> 00:09:42,200
You're not asleep yet?

120
00:09:42,280 --> 00:09:44,840
I thought you'd gone upstairs already.

121
00:09:46,720 --> 00:09:48,960
Have you been doing this for a long time?

122
00:09:50,880 --> 00:09:53,440
You mean the spirit offering?

123
00:09:53,520 --> 00:09:56,080
What kind of offering is that?

124
00:09:56,160 --> 00:09:57,480
The chant you were reciting

125
00:09:57,560 --> 00:10:00,600
sounded strange. It made me uncomfortable.

126
00:10:00,680 --> 00:10:03,840
It's called a protection chant
for the house.

127
00:10:04,560 --> 00:10:06,400
I don't chant it often,

128
00:10:06,480 --> 00:10:08,480
so you're probably just not used to it.

129
00:10:09,080 --> 00:10:11,520
Anong, listen to me.

130
00:10:11,600 --> 00:10:15,320
Just because I allowed you
to build a storage room,

131
00:10:15,400 --> 00:10:18,080
plant trees and flowers however you like,

132
00:10:18,160 --> 00:10:21,680
doesn't mean
you can do things behind my back

133
00:10:21,760 --> 00:10:23,680
and go too far.

134
00:10:24,280 --> 00:10:26,480
You've been with me for years. You know

135
00:10:26,560 --> 00:10:28,320
I don't believe in

136
00:10:28,400 --> 00:10:30,360
mediums or spirit possession
or any of that.

137
00:10:31,360 --> 00:10:34,680
That's going too far.
There's no spirit possession.

138
00:10:34,760 --> 00:10:37,560
I'm just making an offering
to the guardian spirit.

139
00:10:37,640 --> 00:10:39,840
But if you don't like it,

140
00:10:39,920 --> 00:10:42,000
I won't do it anymore.

141
00:10:44,440 --> 00:10:46,680
Tomorrow's your birthday.

142
00:10:47,280 --> 00:10:49,360
I've already prepared everything

143
00:10:49,440 --> 00:10:52,360
for your merit making.

144
00:10:55,480 --> 00:10:56,480
That's why

145
00:10:56,560 --> 00:11:00,000
I made such a big offering
to the guardian spirit.

146
00:11:00,080 --> 00:11:02,880
I want them to protect you.

147
00:11:08,840 --> 00:11:10,520
That's a strange way of caring.

148
00:11:11,360 --> 00:11:14,240
Next time,
if you're going to do something like this,

149
00:11:14,320 --> 00:11:16,600
just make merit, give alms, say prayers.
That's enough.

150
00:11:17,320 --> 00:11:20,120
And if you're going to make an offering,
keep it simple.

151
00:11:20,200 --> 00:11:22,600
No need to go to extremes like this.

152
00:11:22,680 --> 00:11:23,600
Yes.

153
00:11:33,840 --> 00:11:38,840
Still, thank you
for preparing my birthday.

154
00:11:39,360 --> 00:11:42,120
I'm always happy to do things for you.

155
00:11:42,200 --> 00:11:43,680
You know that, right?

156
00:11:44,280 --> 00:11:47,920
Earlier today, I met Warat.

157
00:11:48,000 --> 00:11:49,120
Really?

158
00:11:49,640 --> 00:11:50,840
That's good, isn't it?

159
00:11:50,920 --> 00:11:54,400
Anyway, get some rest tonight.

160
00:11:54,480 --> 00:11:56,000
We're going to make merit
early tomorrow, right?

161
00:11:56,080 --> 00:11:57,360
Yes.

162
00:11:58,040 --> 00:11:59,200
I'm going to rest now.

163
00:12:14,080 --> 00:12:15,280
BAAN SAENG WAN MAI

164
00:12:15,360 --> 00:12:16,760
WELCOME ALL OUR GENEROUS BENEFACTORS

165
00:12:16,840 --> 00:12:18,240
Is this tray big enough?

166
00:12:18,320 --> 00:12:19,800
Oh, thank you.

167
00:12:19,880 --> 00:12:22,360
I'll have
the one who ordered check it again.

168
00:12:22,440 --> 00:12:24,520
I'm just here to deliver it.

169
00:12:24,600 --> 00:12:26,080
Oh? Aren't you the birthday host?

170
00:12:26,160 --> 00:12:27,200
No, ma'am.

171
00:12:27,280 --> 00:12:29,680
-I'm sorry.
-But they should be arriving soon.

172
00:12:29,760 --> 00:12:31,600
Then you can put the rest over there.

173
00:12:31,680 --> 00:12:33,520
-Sure, no problem.
-Thank you.

174
00:12:35,640 --> 00:12:39,000
Mom, the donor hasn't arrived yet.

175
00:12:39,080 --> 00:12:40,680
So I told them to set everything up first.

176
00:12:40,760 --> 00:12:43,000
Are you going to work by yourself today,

177
00:12:43,080 --> 00:12:46,160
-or is Mr. Arnon picking you up?
-I'm waiting for him.

178
00:12:46,240 --> 00:12:49,040
He's taking forever.
I don't know if he overslept.

179
00:12:49,120 --> 00:12:50,080
Hey.

180
00:12:50,160 --> 00:12:52,360
You're always complaining.

181
00:12:52,440 --> 00:12:53,640
Unbelievable.

182
00:12:53,720 --> 00:12:54,680
There he is.

183
00:12:54,760 --> 00:12:57,080
Speak of the devil.

184
00:12:57,160 --> 00:12:58,480
Mama Toi, good morning.

185
00:12:58,560 --> 00:13:00,240
Good morning, Mr. Arnon.

186
00:13:01,360 --> 00:13:04,080
Oh, donations this early?

187
00:13:04,160 --> 00:13:06,000
Yes, it's for a birthday.

188
00:13:06,080 --> 00:13:08,400
But it looks like
they've never been here before.

189
00:13:08,480 --> 00:13:09,960
They called our staff

190
00:13:10,040 --> 00:13:12,520
and said they got lost.

191
00:13:13,120 --> 00:13:17,040
But Baan Saeng Wan Mai
isn't that hard to find.

192
00:13:17,120 --> 00:13:18,960
Maybe they really
haven't been here before.

193
00:13:19,800 --> 00:13:20,960
Let me help.

194
00:13:21,040 --> 00:13:22,720
MS. ANONG

195
00:13:24,160 --> 00:13:25,280
What is it?

196
00:13:27,480 --> 00:13:28,720
Is this the donor's name?

197
00:13:29,720 --> 00:13:31,520
Yes. Ms. Anong.

198
00:13:37,240 --> 00:13:40,560
Is something wrong?
Why do you two look so strange?

199
00:13:44,840 --> 00:13:46,160
Ah, they might be here.

200
00:13:47,680 --> 00:13:50,800
Yes, that must be them.
I'll go take care of them.

201
00:13:50,880 --> 00:13:54,200
You two hurry to work
or you'll hit traffic.

202
00:13:54,720 --> 00:13:56,040
Thanks for always coming to pick her up.

203
00:13:56,120 --> 00:13:57,320
Of course.

204
00:14:04,400 --> 00:14:07,120
Let's be a little late for work today.

205
00:14:07,800 --> 00:14:09,120
I'm so ready.

206
00:14:09,200 --> 00:14:10,360
Are you ready?

207
00:14:10,440 --> 00:14:11,800
No.

208
00:14:11,880 --> 00:14:13,640
And I don't want to be.

209
00:14:14,680 --> 00:14:17,200
But if we don't confess first,

210
00:14:17,280 --> 00:14:19,560
Jirasin will definitely
come down hard on us.

211
00:14:20,080 --> 00:14:22,600
But what we did last night wasn't right.

212
00:14:22,680 --> 00:14:25,240
We searched through
Grandma's private office.

213
00:14:25,320 --> 00:14:26,880
I've been thinking all night.

214
00:14:26,960 --> 00:14:29,040
There's no way she'll forgive us.

215
00:14:29,120 --> 00:14:30,800
Then don't think about it.

216
00:14:30,880 --> 00:14:32,760
We have two choices. One,

217
00:14:34,000 --> 00:14:35,280
Jirasin exposes us completely.

218
00:14:35,360 --> 00:14:38,800
Two, we confess ourselves.

219
00:14:39,360 --> 00:14:41,120
Come on. Maybe when we get there,

220
00:14:41,200 --> 00:14:43,440
Grandma won't even be at the table.

221
00:15:08,600 --> 00:15:09,960
Grandma, I'm sorry…

222
00:15:11,520 --> 00:15:12,920
for being rude.

223
00:15:13,520 --> 00:15:15,080
Sorry?

224
00:15:16,800 --> 00:15:18,680
Which one should you sorry about first?

225
00:15:19,800 --> 00:15:20,840
Sorry

226
00:15:21,360 --> 00:15:24,960
for walking away from the table
while I was still speaking?

227
00:15:26,680 --> 00:15:27,800
Or

228
00:15:28,320 --> 00:15:31,200
sorry for going into my office

229
00:15:31,280 --> 00:15:33,280
without asking for permission?

230
00:15:33,960 --> 00:15:35,320
How did you know?

231
00:15:36,040 --> 00:15:40,400
You thought you disabled all the CCTV
in the office, right?

232
00:15:47,440 --> 00:15:48,920
I had my reasons.

233
00:15:49,000 --> 00:15:52,440
But you do know that legally,

234
00:15:52,520 --> 00:15:55,800
Vanich Mall can take
serious action against you.

235
00:15:57,320 --> 00:15:59,040
That's up to you.

236
00:16:01,320 --> 00:16:03,400
But I've thought it through.

237
00:16:04,200 --> 00:16:06,080
Whatever I did…

238
00:16:06,160 --> 00:16:07,920
It was my fault.

239
00:16:08,000 --> 00:16:11,440
I was the one who suggested
going into your office.

240
00:16:11,520 --> 00:16:12,560
She has nothing to do with it.

241
00:16:13,240 --> 00:16:14,760
I forced her.

242
00:16:15,960 --> 00:16:18,800
You two really love each other, don't you?

243
00:16:19,360 --> 00:16:21,160
You're competing to see who goes to jail.

244
00:16:22,240 --> 00:16:25,160
Let me ask you this.
Are you threatening me?

245
00:16:26,040 --> 00:16:27,720
If we were afraid,

246
00:16:27,800 --> 00:16:29,960
we wouldn't have dared to do this.

247
00:16:31,320 --> 00:16:32,440
Do you see now?

248
00:16:32,520 --> 00:16:35,760
This is what happens
when you refuse to tell me the truth.

249
00:16:35,840 --> 00:16:36,960
Warat.

250
00:16:38,160 --> 00:16:40,600
I suppose

251
00:16:41,200 --> 00:16:45,440
I'll have to teach you two a lesson.

252
00:16:45,520 --> 00:16:47,440
Otherwise, you'll get carried away

253
00:16:48,160 --> 00:16:50,840
and keep doing foolish things.

254
00:16:54,120 --> 00:16:55,240
Go ahead.

255
00:16:55,880 --> 00:16:57,360
Do it, Grandma.

256
00:16:57,440 --> 00:16:59,480
Take it all the way to court.

257
00:17:00,920 --> 00:17:03,880
Let everyone see why I had to do this.

258
00:17:04,520 --> 00:17:07,119
Let them see the truth
behind your success,

259
00:17:07,200 --> 00:17:09,520
how many generations of your own family

260
00:17:09,599 --> 00:17:10,839
have suffered for it!

261
00:17:10,920 --> 00:17:12,680
Ugh! Stop it, Warat.

262
00:17:13,960 --> 00:17:15,720
I'm your grandmother.

263
00:17:16,800 --> 00:17:19,119
Thanks for the reminder. I almost forgot.

264
00:17:19,200 --> 00:17:20,000
Warat!

265
00:17:23,200 --> 00:17:24,800
That's enough, Warat.

266
00:17:25,400 --> 00:17:26,839
Please excuse us.

267
00:17:26,920 --> 00:17:27,880
Let's go.

268
00:17:28,400 --> 00:17:29,240
Warat.

269
00:17:29,320 --> 00:17:30,720
Warat, please.

270
00:17:31,960 --> 00:17:32,840
Let's go.

271
00:17:44,760 --> 00:17:47,160
Let's give these to the kids.

272
00:17:47,240 --> 00:17:49,560
Everyone, come get it.

273
00:17:49,640 --> 00:17:50,760
We have drinks and sweets.

274
00:17:50,840 --> 00:17:52,120
It's not that Anong.

275
00:17:52,200 --> 00:17:54,560
She has never called
asking about anyone here,

276
00:17:54,640 --> 00:17:56,200
and has never been here.

277
00:17:56,280 --> 00:17:58,320
Case closed. Let's go.

278
00:17:58,400 --> 00:18:00,680
We can finally go back to work in peace.

279
00:18:01,400 --> 00:18:03,000
All that excitement for nothing.

280
00:18:03,600 --> 00:18:04,440
-Let's go.
-Alright.

281
00:18:05,960 --> 00:18:08,000
Here, I'll carry it.

282
00:18:10,360 --> 00:18:11,200
I wonder why.

283
00:18:11,280 --> 00:18:15,440
When my bag is on you, it looks…

284
00:18:16,120 --> 00:18:17,080
terrible.

285
00:18:23,760 --> 00:18:24,840
I'm hurt.

286
00:18:26,360 --> 00:18:28,560
I'm kidding. It's cute.

287
00:18:28,640 --> 00:18:30,200
Come on, let's go to work.

288
00:18:31,480 --> 00:18:33,480
Yes. Take it.

289
00:18:33,560 --> 00:18:35,960
BAAN SAENG WAN MAI
WELCOME ALL OUR GENEROUS BENEFACTORS

290
00:18:39,280 --> 00:18:41,120
Is this Baan Saeng Wan Mai?

291
00:18:42,480 --> 00:18:45,720
Yes. This is the place I called yesterday.

292
00:18:47,240 --> 00:18:51,640
Since it's your birthday,
I wanted to surprise you.

293
00:19:22,080 --> 00:19:23,960
So where exactly are we going?

294
00:19:24,040 --> 00:19:26,720
You've had me driving around for ages now.

295
00:19:27,680 --> 00:19:28,760
Just keep driving.

296
00:19:29,360 --> 00:19:34,120
And what if I drive
and something suddenly appears?

297
00:19:34,200 --> 00:19:35,920
What are you going to do?

298
00:19:36,000 --> 00:19:38,840
Didn't you say you were scared
to ride in a car I'm driving?

299
00:19:39,440 --> 00:19:41,440
I've got nothing left to be afraid of now.

300
00:19:41,960 --> 00:19:44,520
Besides, with your focus that scattered,

301
00:19:46,000 --> 00:19:48,320
you probably don't have the energy
to connect with anything.

302
00:19:49,600 --> 00:19:51,080
Or if you're not okay, we can pull over.

303
00:19:51,160 --> 00:19:52,440
I'll just take a taxi.

304
00:19:53,640 --> 00:19:56,120
Hey, that's not what I meant.

305
00:19:56,200 --> 00:19:59,480
Well… Fine, I'll drive.

306
00:19:59,560 --> 00:20:03,240
But if I randomly end up somewhere weird,

307
00:20:03,320 --> 00:20:05,520
don't scold me.

308
00:20:11,920 --> 00:20:16,000
So what are you going to do about Grandma?

309
00:20:16,080 --> 00:20:19,360
Is there anything I can help you with?

310
00:20:19,440 --> 00:20:22,280
I guess I'll just let things go.

311
00:20:22,360 --> 00:20:24,640
By now, Jirasin has probably already

312
00:20:24,720 --> 00:20:26,960
taken those photos to Grandma.

313
00:20:29,080 --> 00:20:30,800
Even if Grandma believes him,

314
00:20:30,880 --> 00:20:33,640
she wouldn't be cruel to you.
You're her real grandson.

315
00:20:34,160 --> 00:20:36,800
A real grandson she's never cared about?

316
00:20:37,600 --> 00:20:39,120
Mr. Warat,

317
00:20:39,200 --> 00:20:41,520
when I was alone with her,

318
00:20:41,600 --> 00:20:43,680
she kept talking about you.

319
00:20:43,760 --> 00:20:45,240
Do you want to hear?

320
00:20:45,920 --> 00:20:47,840
If I didn't hear it with my own ears,

321
00:20:48,400 --> 00:20:51,120
I won't believe you anyway. Waste of time.

322
00:20:51,200 --> 00:20:52,520
Okay.

323
00:20:53,040 --> 00:20:56,440
I won't say anything then.
You'll accuse me of siding with Grandma

324
00:20:56,520 --> 00:20:57,680
or being naive again.

325
00:20:58,760 --> 00:21:01,520
You've played a part
in making me better, you know.

326
00:21:01,600 --> 00:21:03,280
A better person.

327
00:21:03,360 --> 00:21:04,240
Thank you.

328
00:21:04,320 --> 00:21:06,040
Me?

329
00:21:06,120 --> 00:21:07,600
Yes.

330
00:21:13,680 --> 00:21:15,120
These are for the kids.

331
00:21:16,960 --> 00:21:19,520
Enjoy it.

332
00:21:19,600 --> 00:21:20,560
We keep things

333
00:21:20,640 --> 00:21:23,800
pretty small here,
so it's easier to take care of everyone.

334
00:21:24,560 --> 00:21:26,640
That's good. My husband and I

335
00:21:26,720 --> 00:21:29,520
like supporting
small orphanages like this.

336
00:21:30,320 --> 00:21:32,560
It's not crowded. It feels more private.

337
00:21:32,640 --> 00:21:36,240
Thank you on behalf of the children.

338
00:21:36,320 --> 00:21:38,720
Please come register

339
00:21:38,800 --> 00:21:41,520
so we can issue a donation receipt.

340
00:21:41,600 --> 00:21:44,280
We prefer to donate anonymously.

341
00:21:45,360 --> 00:21:49,720
Of course. I'll prepare
documents without your name.

342
00:21:49,800 --> 00:21:50,880
This way, please.

343
00:21:50,960 --> 00:21:53,960
A friend of mine
once adopted a child from here,

344
00:21:54,040 --> 00:21:55,680
but that was a long time ago.

345
00:21:55,760 --> 00:21:59,760
That child should be around
20, maybe 25 now.

346
00:21:59,840 --> 00:22:02,200
But we lost contact.

347
00:22:03,800 --> 00:22:06,160
It's really been a long time.

348
00:22:06,240 --> 00:22:11,240
If they're that age, they've probably
gone out to live their own life.

349
00:22:11,320 --> 00:22:15,000
But most of them
still keep in touch with us

350
00:22:16,520 --> 00:22:19,360
So you still have contact information
for most of them?

351
00:22:19,440 --> 00:22:21,320
Yes, almost all of them.

352
00:22:21,400 --> 00:22:23,920
What was the child's name?

353
00:22:30,000 --> 00:22:31,480
I don't remember.

354
00:22:35,200 --> 00:22:36,760
Thank you.

355
00:22:38,720 --> 00:22:39,720
This way, please.

356
00:22:43,200 --> 00:22:44,600
This is Mama Toi,

357
00:22:44,680 --> 00:22:47,000
the founder and manager here.

358
00:22:47,920 --> 00:22:48,760
Hello.

359
00:22:48,840 --> 00:22:49,760
Hello.

360
00:22:49,840 --> 00:22:51,360
Happy birthday.

361
00:22:52,080 --> 00:22:53,840
Thank you very much.

362
00:22:53,920 --> 00:22:55,840
The children here are lovely.

363
00:22:55,920 --> 00:22:57,920
They're hardworking and help one another.

364
00:22:58,000 --> 00:22:58,840
Yes.

365
00:22:59,840 --> 00:23:03,400
Anong, what were you two talking about?

366
00:23:03,480 --> 00:23:07,560
The staff are already handing out food
and snacks to the kids.

367
00:23:08,560 --> 00:23:10,440
Sorry.

368
00:23:10,520 --> 00:23:14,040
She was asking about the kids here.

369
00:23:14,840 --> 00:23:15,680
The kids here?

370
00:23:18,600 --> 00:23:20,480
Let's go give food to the kids.

371
00:23:25,360 --> 00:23:30,840
BAAN SAENG WAN MAI

372
00:23:30,920 --> 00:23:32,200
Wait, wait. Stop.

373
00:23:38,840 --> 00:23:41,160
I've seen this girl at home before.

374
00:23:41,240 --> 00:23:42,400
She came with Warat.

375
00:23:45,840 --> 00:23:47,800
Who is this young lady?

376
00:23:48,320 --> 00:23:49,560
Me?

377
00:23:52,640 --> 00:23:54,560
Why are you laughing?

378
00:23:55,680 --> 00:23:58,960
It's true. You keep making my life better.

379
00:23:59,040 --> 00:24:00,880
I'm lucky to have you.

380
00:24:00,960 --> 00:24:03,960
Thank you. I'm honored

381
00:24:04,040 --> 00:24:06,360
that my life makes yours better.

382
00:24:06,440 --> 00:24:10,680
But I laughed
because I envy your life too.

383
00:24:10,760 --> 00:24:11,640
Mine?

384
00:24:12,840 --> 00:24:14,400
What's there to envy?

385
00:24:16,600 --> 00:24:21,880
You're smart enough to know
your life is heaven-sent.

386
00:24:22,880 --> 00:24:24,280
Your looks,

387
00:24:24,360 --> 00:24:26,440
your career, your family background.

388
00:24:26,520 --> 00:24:27,560
Then switch lives with me.

389
00:24:28,160 --> 00:24:30,800
-No.
-Oh? Why reject it so fast?

390
00:24:31,640 --> 00:24:33,800
You can't measure life like that.

391
00:24:33,880 --> 00:24:35,800
Even if I like your life,

392
00:24:35,880 --> 00:24:38,240
I admire how good your life is,

393
00:24:38,320 --> 00:24:41,200
it doesn't mean I want to be you. Right?

394
00:24:41,280 --> 00:24:43,400
I'm satisfied with who I am.

395
00:24:46,920 --> 00:24:48,200
You have a great attitude.

396
00:24:50,120 --> 00:24:52,200
Mama Toi raised you well.

397
00:24:52,800 --> 00:24:53,800
Of course.

398
00:24:56,200 --> 00:24:58,760
If we were really dating, that'd be nice.

399
00:24:59,560 --> 00:25:00,560
Yeah.

400
00:25:16,080 --> 00:25:18,240
I mean, no.

401
00:25:18,320 --> 00:25:19,720
I mean no.

402
00:25:19,800 --> 00:25:21,360
I misspoke.

403
00:25:21,440 --> 00:25:22,880
Why not?

404
00:25:22,960 --> 00:25:25,040
It would be nice, right?

405
00:25:25,880 --> 00:25:28,920
No. Who says that so bluntly like that?

406
00:25:29,000 --> 00:25:31,600
Then how am I supposed to say it?

407
00:25:34,160 --> 00:25:36,520
I'm not talking to you anymore. I'm out.

408
00:25:37,280 --> 00:25:38,600
Kluay, wait.

409
00:25:39,600 --> 00:25:41,480
Where are you going? The car's this way.

410
00:25:48,720 --> 00:25:49,800
Let's go home.

411
00:25:49,880 --> 00:25:51,760
-Wait.
-What?

412
00:25:51,840 --> 00:25:53,560
Why are your cheeks red?

413
00:25:54,360 --> 00:25:56,840
I ate too much lycopene.

414
00:25:58,640 --> 00:25:59,480
Wow, Kluay.

415
00:26:00,360 --> 00:26:01,480
Fine, let's go.

416
00:26:02,560 --> 00:26:03,440
Hey.

417
00:26:05,200 --> 00:26:07,800
You're still thinking
about Mama Toi's daughter?

418
00:26:07,880 --> 00:26:09,600
Are you sure

419
00:26:09,680 --> 00:26:11,880
Kluay is just an orphan

420
00:26:11,960 --> 00:26:13,960
that the orphanage owner took in?

421
00:26:14,960 --> 00:26:16,360
Of course.

422
00:26:16,440 --> 00:26:18,080
I just asked

423
00:26:18,160 --> 00:26:22,200
the old security guard here.

424
00:26:23,160 --> 00:26:25,240
But why did Mama Toi speak as if

425
00:26:25,320 --> 00:26:28,800
Kluay were her real daughter?

426
00:26:30,640 --> 00:26:32,920
Who is this young lady?

427
00:26:33,000 --> 00:26:34,880
She's my daughter.

428
00:26:34,960 --> 00:26:36,520
-Boonsita.
-Oh.

429
00:26:36,600 --> 00:26:39,160
Kluay is a volunteer here.

430
00:26:39,240 --> 00:26:41,880
Where did you meet her before?

431
00:26:42,760 --> 00:26:45,040
-Well…
-We've never met her.

432
00:26:45,560 --> 00:26:47,280
Maybe she looks like someone we know.

433
00:26:49,120 --> 00:26:50,680
What a coincidence.

434
00:26:51,720 --> 00:26:55,120
Why did you have to lie
to her like that, Anong?

435
00:26:55,960 --> 00:26:58,120
Do you think we'll never see her again?

436
00:26:58,760 --> 00:27:00,640
That could make us look bad.

437
00:27:01,240 --> 00:27:05,280
Why didn't we just tell her we've met
that girl Kluay before?

438
00:27:08,880 --> 00:27:11,520
Why are you so concerned about it?

439
00:27:12,040 --> 00:27:14,520
She's just an orphan.

440
00:27:15,600 --> 00:27:17,360
What do you mean by that, Anong?

441
00:27:17,880 --> 00:27:19,960
What are you thinking?
I don't understand you at all.

442
00:27:28,200 --> 00:27:30,880
Don't worry about what I'm thinking.

443
00:27:30,960 --> 00:27:33,080
You should be
more concerned about Mr. Warat

444
00:27:33,160 --> 00:27:35,280
and that girl Kluay.

445
00:27:40,400 --> 00:27:41,240
That's true.

446
00:27:42,240 --> 00:27:43,520
This is a big deal.

447
00:27:43,600 --> 00:27:47,880
Someone like Warat
should have a life partner

448
00:27:47,960 --> 00:27:51,120
who's more suitable, better than Kluay.

449
00:27:51,200 --> 00:27:52,680
She's not suitable for him at all.

450
00:28:02,680 --> 00:28:05,160
<i>She was around</i>
<i>three years old back then, right?</i>

451
00:28:05,240 --> 00:28:06,920
<i>How would I remember that?</i>

452
00:28:07,000 --> 00:28:08,520
<i>Just stop dragging me into this.</i>

453
00:28:08,600 --> 00:28:11,360
<i>I don't want</i>
<i>to get involved with you either.</i>

454
00:28:11,880 --> 00:28:14,120
<i>But this has to be settled.</i>

455
00:28:14,840 --> 00:28:18,760
<i>Or do you want this to circle back to you?</i>

456
00:28:18,840 --> 00:28:21,360
<i>If I go down, do you think</i>

457
00:28:21,440 --> 00:28:23,880
<i>you won't go down with me?</i>

458
00:28:23,960 --> 00:28:25,600
<i>No need to threaten me.</i>

459
00:28:25,680 --> 00:28:27,720
<i>That girl was around three,</i>

460
00:28:27,800 --> 00:28:30,120
<i>like you said. End of story.</i>

461
00:28:30,200 --> 00:28:31,560
<i>Are you sure?</i>

462
00:28:32,200 --> 00:28:36,160
<i>So she'd be about 24 or 25 now.</i>

463
00:28:36,240 --> 00:28:38,600
<i>What? You've found her?</i>

464
00:28:38,680 --> 00:28:40,400
<i>Just tell me what you want.</i>

465
00:28:40,480 --> 00:28:42,160
<i>I'll find someone to help.</i>

466
00:28:43,480 --> 00:28:45,120
<i>You're getting scared now, aren't you?</i>

467
00:28:46,560 --> 00:28:47,760
<i>Good.</i>

468
00:28:47,840 --> 00:28:50,000
<i>Make sure it's the right person.</i>

469
00:28:53,480 --> 00:28:55,480
Mama Toi's daughter?

470
00:28:55,560 --> 00:28:57,360
You mean Som?

471
00:28:58,120 --> 00:29:00,560
Not that one. The other one.

472
00:29:00,640 --> 00:29:03,360
There isn't another.
Mama Toi only has one daughter.

473
00:29:03,880 --> 00:29:05,360
Oh, wait.

474
00:29:05,440 --> 00:29:08,080
There's an adopted daughter named Kluay.

475
00:29:08,160 --> 00:29:10,200
Do her biological parents

476
00:29:10,280 --> 00:29:11,880
ever come visit?

477
00:29:11,960 --> 00:29:13,680
That was a long time ago.

478
00:29:13,760 --> 00:29:17,000
From what I remember, her parents died.

479
00:29:17,080 --> 00:29:18,920
I think it was a car accident.

480
00:29:19,000 --> 00:29:22,680
<i>So Mama Toi and Papa Wichai adopted her.</i>

481
00:29:33,280 --> 00:29:34,640
How was it?

482
00:29:36,160 --> 00:29:37,640
Did you find out anything?

483
00:29:38,160 --> 00:29:41,320
So what exactly is going on
between Kluay and Warat?

484
00:29:41,400 --> 00:29:44,280
What kind of relationship do they have?

485
00:29:45,760 --> 00:29:49,440
We should let Sin handle it.

486
00:29:49,960 --> 00:29:53,360
Those two already have
unfinished business between them.

487
00:29:55,560 --> 00:29:58,240
I won't waste my time calling him.

488
00:29:58,320 --> 00:30:00,000
You saw it last night, didn't you?

489
00:30:00,080 --> 00:30:02,280
He almost ran me over.

490
00:30:02,360 --> 00:30:04,040
He barely missed.

491
00:30:04,120 --> 00:30:05,800
Good thing I dodged in time.

492
00:30:08,080 --> 00:30:12,200
I thought you weren't holding a grudge.

493
00:30:13,200 --> 00:30:14,080
Anong.

494
00:30:14,600 --> 00:30:17,480
Just because I don't say how I feel
doesn't mean

495
00:30:18,000 --> 00:30:20,200
I've forgotten what your nephew did.

496
00:30:20,960 --> 00:30:22,640
If he doesn't want to live in this house,

497
00:30:22,720 --> 00:30:25,160
I'll throw him out for good.

498
00:30:25,760 --> 00:30:26,920
No, you can't.

499
00:30:27,440 --> 00:30:28,760
Please don't.

500
00:30:28,840 --> 00:30:30,600
I promised Naree

501
00:30:30,680 --> 00:30:32,720
I'd raise her son the best I could.

502
00:30:32,800 --> 00:30:35,720
Please don't make me break my word.

503
00:30:35,800 --> 00:30:38,800
If you're still angry at Sin,

504
00:30:38,880 --> 00:30:40,840
I… I'll call him.

505
00:30:40,920 --> 00:30:43,640
I'll make him apologize right now.

506
00:30:43,720 --> 00:30:44,960
No need.

507
00:30:46,040 --> 00:30:48,120
I'm not sending him far away.

508
00:30:48,640 --> 00:30:50,240
Just to the storage room.

509
00:30:54,840 --> 00:30:56,080
The storage room?

510
00:30:57,840 --> 00:30:59,720
Yes, your storage room.

511
00:30:59,800 --> 00:31:02,440
I've never seen you
actually store anything there.

512
00:31:02,520 --> 00:31:06,680
Go clean it up. Anything damaged,
sell it off.

513
00:31:07,360 --> 00:31:10,120
I'm doing this
because the contractor suggested it.

514
00:31:10,200 --> 00:31:12,280
Look. We need to drive in more piles

515
00:31:12,800 --> 00:31:14,400
for stability.

516
00:31:15,520 --> 00:31:18,200
It's not for that ungrateful brat.

517
00:31:19,280 --> 00:31:20,560
No, you can't.

518
00:31:22,920 --> 00:31:25,000
Are you not listening, Anong?

519
00:31:26,120 --> 00:31:28,040
I told you, I'm not kicking him out.

520
00:31:28,120 --> 00:31:29,920
I'll just let him stay
in the storage room.

521
00:31:30,000 --> 00:31:32,120
Clean it up.

522
00:31:32,640 --> 00:31:33,920
If you don't,

523
00:31:34,000 --> 00:31:36,160
I'll have someone
tear everything out myself.

524
00:31:38,280 --> 00:31:39,360
Understood?

525
00:31:54,080 --> 00:31:55,400
Other than you,

526
00:31:55,480 --> 00:31:57,520
Warat, and Kluay,

527
00:31:57,600 --> 00:31:59,600
does anyone else know about this?

528
00:32:00,800 --> 00:32:01,800
No one.

529
00:32:01,880 --> 00:32:03,120
It's a serious matter,

530
00:32:03,200 --> 00:32:05,080
so I came to inform you.

531
00:32:05,160 --> 00:32:06,560
Thank you

532
00:32:06,640 --> 00:32:08,840
for looking out for me.

533
00:32:09,600 --> 00:32:10,760
Yes.

534
00:32:10,840 --> 00:32:11,880
From now on,

535
00:32:11,960 --> 00:32:14,360
I may have to use legal measures

536
00:32:14,440 --> 00:32:17,000
to discipline Warat properly.

537
00:32:17,080 --> 00:32:18,800
I can't let this continue.

538
00:32:21,160 --> 00:32:23,000
Uh, if you do that,

539
00:32:23,760 --> 00:32:25,960
it could damage

540
00:32:26,480 --> 00:32:28,480
the investors' trust.

541
00:32:29,520 --> 00:32:30,440
Have a seat.

542
00:32:30,520 --> 00:32:31,520
Thank you.

543
00:32:33,400 --> 00:32:35,120
But in terms of reputation,

544
00:32:35,200 --> 00:32:37,600
there may be benefits too.

545
00:32:37,680 --> 00:32:40,440
Handling it legally could actually

546
00:32:40,520 --> 00:32:42,840
increase investors' confidence.

547
00:32:42,920 --> 00:32:45,720
They'd see our transparency

548
00:32:45,800 --> 00:32:47,640
and integrity.

549
00:32:47,720 --> 00:32:49,720
If someone's wrong, they're wrong.

550
00:32:50,240 --> 00:32:52,160
Wouldn't that be better?

551
00:32:54,040 --> 00:32:55,040
No.

552
00:32:56,240 --> 00:32:59,320
I told you everything

553
00:32:59,400 --> 00:33:00,760
because

554
00:33:00,840 --> 00:33:02,360
I want you

555
00:33:02,440 --> 00:33:04,360
to understand
Mr. Warat's problem more clearly.

556
00:33:04,960 --> 00:33:06,720
Please be patient a little longer.

557
00:33:06,800 --> 00:33:08,960
If Mr. Warat becomes the chairman

558
00:33:09,040 --> 00:33:10,880
and inherits everything,

559
00:33:11,400 --> 00:33:13,080
he'll understand things better.

560
00:33:13,160 --> 00:33:14,880
But Warat isn't someone who cares about

561
00:33:14,960 --> 00:33:16,840
wealth or property.

562
00:33:16,920 --> 00:33:18,120
I know.

563
00:33:18,640 --> 00:33:21,440
But I believe his sense of responsibility

564
00:33:21,520 --> 00:33:23,680
will grow with the position he's given.

565
00:33:24,320 --> 00:33:25,840
And honestly,

566
00:33:25,920 --> 00:33:28,240
I see

567
00:33:28,320 --> 00:33:30,240
Mr. Warat as a younger brother.

568
00:33:30,760 --> 00:33:32,480
If he matures

569
00:33:32,560 --> 00:33:34,640
and succeeds in his role,

570
00:33:34,720 --> 00:33:36,480
I'll be happy for him.

571
00:33:43,360 --> 00:33:44,360
Alright.

572
00:33:44,880 --> 00:33:47,240
Let's try your method first.

573
00:33:47,320 --> 00:33:48,960
It won't cause any harm.

574
00:33:50,160 --> 00:33:52,840
Honestly,

575
00:33:52,920 --> 00:33:56,240
I never intended to punish Warat
too harshly anyway.

576
00:33:56,320 --> 00:33:58,640
If I go too far,

577
00:33:58,720 --> 00:34:02,880
it'll only worsen our relationship.

578
00:34:04,680 --> 00:34:07,640
If that's the case,
should I delete all the photos?

579
00:34:07,720 --> 00:34:09,400
Then everything will finally be over.

580
00:34:10,280 --> 00:34:11,199
Thank you.

581
00:34:23,400 --> 00:34:25,199
<i>Delete all the photos?</i>

582
00:34:25,280 --> 00:34:27,360
<i>You finally got a chance</i>
<i>to take them down.</i>

583
00:34:27,440 --> 00:34:29,199
I was going to delete them anyway.

584
00:34:29,280 --> 00:34:31,320
What I'm doing now
is worse than taking them down.

585
00:34:32,120 --> 00:34:33,120
Trust me.

586
00:34:34,760 --> 00:34:36,600
Is it completely broken, Mom?

587
00:34:36,679 --> 00:34:37,520
Okay.

588
00:34:37,600 --> 00:34:40,639
Then I'll call
the CCTV company right away.

589
00:34:41,639 --> 00:34:42,760
And…

590
00:34:42,840 --> 00:34:45,600
Have all the donors already left?
It's so quiet.

591
00:34:48,960 --> 00:34:51,040
This feels so good. Thank you.

592
00:34:51,920 --> 00:34:52,920
Yes, Mom.

593
00:34:53,000 --> 00:34:55,400
Okay. I'll head back early today.

594
00:34:55,480 --> 00:34:57,560
Alright. Love you. Mwah.

595
00:34:59,240 --> 00:35:00,560
Is something wrong?

596
00:35:00,640 --> 00:35:03,320
The CCTV at Baan Saeng Wan Mai is broken.

597
00:35:03,400 --> 00:35:04,920
I might have to leave early.

598
00:35:05,000 --> 00:35:06,560
You don't have to drive me.

599
00:35:06,640 --> 00:35:08,320
How could I not?

600
00:35:08,400 --> 00:35:11,040
If it involves technicians,
I have to help.

601
00:35:12,840 --> 00:35:14,800
You're the sweetest.

602
00:35:20,240 --> 00:35:22,520
Wow, that's a lot of work.

603
00:35:22,600 --> 00:35:24,040
See you at noon.

604
00:35:24,120 --> 00:35:25,240
Boat noodles?

605
00:35:25,320 --> 00:35:26,600
Boat noodles.

606
00:35:27,400 --> 00:35:29,000
-Hey, Arnon.
-Yes?

607
00:35:29,760 --> 00:35:31,080
Well,

608
00:35:32,280 --> 00:35:34,200
about Kluay's anklet,

609
00:35:34,280 --> 00:35:36,360
is there any update yet?

610
00:35:38,280 --> 00:35:41,240
It's a long story.
I'll tell you this evening.

611
00:35:50,600 --> 00:35:52,760
I think you made the right decision.

612
00:35:52,840 --> 00:35:55,200
No matter what happens,

613
00:35:55,280 --> 00:35:57,600
we should always do the right thing.

614
00:35:59,000 --> 00:36:01,560
As long as I'm still the CEO here,

615
00:36:02,080 --> 00:36:04,440
if someone under me like Jirasin

616
00:36:05,080 --> 00:36:08,080
thinks he can beat me
with dirty tricks like this, let him try.

617
00:36:15,280 --> 00:36:16,280
Hello.

618
00:36:17,160 --> 00:36:18,200
Hello.

619
00:36:22,200 --> 00:36:23,520
Mr. Warat, you came at the right time.

620
00:36:23,600 --> 00:36:26,600
Could you please
take Mom to run an errand?

621
00:36:27,600 --> 00:36:29,400
It's better if you go with me.

622
00:36:29,480 --> 00:36:31,880
Let Mr. Warat focus on work.

623
00:36:31,960 --> 00:36:33,800
-Yes.
-Didn't you just arrive?

624
00:36:34,560 --> 00:36:35,560
Yes.

625
00:36:36,160 --> 00:36:37,640
Where's Mr. Supol, Grandma?

626
00:36:37,720 --> 00:36:39,720
Why isn't he here?

627
00:36:39,800 --> 00:36:42,000
Why isn't he doing his job?

628
00:36:42,080 --> 00:36:43,920
Mr. Supol took leave today.

629
00:36:44,000 --> 00:36:45,720
Don't worry.

630
00:36:45,800 --> 00:36:47,760
I'll take good care of Mom.

631
00:36:47,840 --> 00:36:49,440
Rat, go to work.

632
00:36:49,520 --> 00:36:52,960
Sin is just taking me nearby.
We'll be back soon.

633
00:36:53,560 --> 00:36:55,280
Don't you have anything
to talk to me about?

634
00:36:56,400 --> 00:36:57,440
Is it possible

635
00:36:57,960 --> 00:37:00,480
that I don't have anything
to talk to you about?

636
00:37:03,000 --> 00:37:04,160
What a strange question.

637
00:37:05,120 --> 00:37:06,480
Let's go, Sin.

638
00:37:14,560 --> 00:37:16,240
This feels strange.

639
00:37:18,440 --> 00:37:19,480
Very strange.

640
00:37:24,480 --> 00:37:25,640
Oh.

641
00:37:25,720 --> 00:37:27,600
Why are you so startled?

642
00:37:27,680 --> 00:37:28,800
Of course I'm startled.

643
00:37:29,320 --> 00:37:30,440
How are you two here?

644
00:37:30,520 --> 00:37:32,720
I've been looking everywhere.

645
00:37:32,800 --> 00:37:33,960
Is something wrong?

646
00:37:35,360 --> 00:37:36,320
Well,

647
00:37:36,400 --> 00:37:39,000
Somkid, the security guard,
said that yesterday,

648
00:37:39,080 --> 00:37:41,080
you ran into Jirasin and had an argument.

649
00:37:41,160 --> 00:37:42,280
What happened?

650
00:37:43,280 --> 00:37:45,760
Kluay and I snuck into Grandma's office.

651
00:37:46,360 --> 00:37:47,320
We ran into Jirasin there.

652
00:37:48,120 --> 00:37:49,800
And not only that,

653
00:37:49,880 --> 00:37:51,880
he secretly took photos of us.

654
00:37:51,960 --> 00:37:53,320
-Don't say "Huh."
-Hey!

655
00:37:55,400 --> 00:37:57,080
<i>The cycle she's trapped in</i>

656
00:37:57,160 --> 00:37:58,680
<i>is heavy.</i>

657
00:37:58,760 --> 00:38:00,600
Who hurt you?

658
00:38:01,200 --> 00:38:03,080
<i>It wouldn't be fair to Kluay</i>

659
00:38:03,160 --> 00:38:05,760
if we didn't help her
find out about her family

660
00:38:05,840 --> 00:38:07,080
NEXT EPISODE

661
00:38:07,160 --> 00:38:09,800
What are you gonna do with the photos
you secretly took of me and Kluay?

662
00:38:09,880 --> 00:38:11,600
I already forgot about those photos.

663
00:38:11,680 --> 00:38:14,560
If you and Kluay hadn't caused trouble,

664
00:38:14,640 --> 00:38:16,840
would this have come back to you?

665
00:38:17,440 --> 00:38:18,280
Mama Toi,

666
00:38:18,880 --> 00:38:22,080
is this man named Mr. Sarut?

667
00:38:22,160 --> 00:38:23,440
I'm not sure.

668
00:38:23,520 --> 00:38:26,360
He didn't want to disclose his name.

669
00:38:26,880 --> 00:38:29,520
<i>The one who has been following you</i>

670
00:38:29,600 --> 00:38:31,080
<i>was murdered.</i>

671
00:38:31,680 --> 00:38:34,120
The one who's been following me?

672
00:40:57,680 --> 00:40:59,680
Subtitle translation by: Panuwat Baikeawon
